                <head>No. 463.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-01-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 29, 1874</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 71.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch, No. 93, of the 14th instant,
                    relative to Mexican bonds held by citizens of the United States, has been
                    received.</p>
                <p>The statement of those bonds promised to you by Mr. Mejia, the minister of
                    finance of Mexico, will be awaited with interest.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
